<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="115" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Diagnostic description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
Overall dark brown to black, except abdominal terga and sterna (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Costalampys pauper (Olivier) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (G-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543222" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">19B</figureCitation>
), which are dark brown. Pronotal disc (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Costalampys pauper (Olivier) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (G-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543222" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">19F</figureCitation>
) entirely black, pronotal expansions dark brown to black, often with anterior corners slightly lighter. Elytron (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Costalampys pauper (Olivier) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (G-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543222" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">19A</figureCitation>
) dark brown to black, with a pale-yellow longitudinal stripe about 4/5
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as elytra. Legs dark brown to black. Sternum VIII (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Costalampys pauper (Olivier) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (G-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543222" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">19G</figureCitation>
) entirely dark brown, without lateral vitreous spots. Pygidium (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Costalampys pauper (Olivier) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (G-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543222" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">19H</figureCitation>
) entirely dark brown.
</paragraph>
