<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
Pronotum (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Costalampys pauper (Olivier) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (G-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543222" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">19F</figureCitation>
) with sides rounded, divergent posteriorly. Sternum VI without lanterns. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Male.</emphasis>
Total length = 8.9-11.3 mm (aver. 10.1 mm); Pronotal length = 2.3-2.7 mm (aver. 2.5 mm); Pronotal width = 1.8-3.3 mm (aver. 2.55 mm); Elytral length = 7.3-8.8 mm (aver. 8.05 mm); Elytral width = 1.8-2.2 mm (aver. 2.0 mm). Antennomere III (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Costalampys pauper (Olivier) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (G-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543222" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">19E</figureCitation>
) with lamella 3
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than core antennomere. Sternum VIII with posterior margin mucronate. Pygidium (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Costalampys pauper (Olivier) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (G-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543222" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">19H</figureCitation>
) with sides rounded, posterior corners barely visible, posterior margin rounded to almost straight. Syntergite (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Costalampys pauper (Olivier) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (G-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543222" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">19I,J</figureCitation>
) boomerang-shaped (with anterior margin strongly curved). Phallus (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Costalampys pauper (Olivier) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (G-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543222" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">19K-M</figureCitation>
) with dorsal plate curved dorsally in lateral view. Paramere apex almost straight, ventral projection (lateral view) moderately developed, almost right-angled. Paramere apex curved ventrally, ventral projection (lateral view) moderately developed, rounded to almost right-angled. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Female</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Costalampys pauper (Olivier) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (G-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543222" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">19C, D</figureCitation>
). Total length = 11.0-11.3 mm (aver. 11.15 mm); Pronotal length = 1.7-1.8 mm (aver. 1.75 mm); Pronotal width = 2.7-2.8 mm (aver. 2.75 mm); Elytral length = 7.2-8.7 mm (aver. 7.95 mm); Elytral width = 2.0-2.5 mm (aver. 2.25 mm). Antennomeres (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Costalampys pauper (Olivier) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (G-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543222" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">19C, D</figureCitation>
) III-X with apical corners almost right-angled, not projected and pointed.
</paragraph>
