<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="115" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
<bibRefCitation author="Olivier, E" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" pagination="86 - 93" refId="B43" refString="Olivier, E, 1899. Contribution a l'etude des Lampyrides [Col.], descriptions et observations. Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France 4: 86 - 93" title="Contribution a l'etude des Lampyrides [Col.], descriptions et observations." volume="4" year="1899">Olivier (1899)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" baseAuthorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Cladodes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cladodes pauper" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pauper">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Cladodes pauper</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Brazil - the syntype we studied is from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Teresópolis">Teresopolis</normalizedToken>
, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil. In addition to 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Teresópolis">Teresopolis</normalizedToken>
, in the 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
Serra dos 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Órgãos">Orgaos</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
mountain range, we found previously unreported populations at the 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Serra da Mantiqueira</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Maciço">Macico</normalizedToken>
da Pedra Branca
</emphasis>
mountain ranges, in the states of Rio de Janeiro and Minas Gerais. Our study provides detailed geographic information for the first time, and expands considerably the known range of the species. After our phylogenetic analysis (see section 3.2), we transfer 
<taxonomicName authorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" baseAuthorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Cladodes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cladodes pauper" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pauper">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Cladodes pauper</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName authority="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" authorityName="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Costalampys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Costalampys" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Costalampys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">gen. nov.</emphasis>
, therefore 
<taxonomicName authority="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" authorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Olivier" baseAuthorityYear="1899" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Costalampys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Costalampys pauper" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pauper">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Costalampys pauper</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Olivier, 1899). 
<bibRefCitation author="Olivier, E" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" pagination="86 - 93" refId="B43" refString="Olivier, E, 1899. Contribution a l'etude des Lampyrides [Col.], descriptions et observations. Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France 4: 86 - 93" title="Contribution a l'etude des Lampyrides [Col.], descriptions et observations." volume="4" year="1899">Olivier (1899)</bibRefCitation>
<normalizedToken originalValue="didn’t">didn't</normalizedToken>
provide an etymology for 
<taxonomicName authority="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" authorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Olivier" baseAuthorityYear="1899" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Costalampys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Costalampys pauper" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pauper">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Costalampys pauper</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but we assume it was based on the Latin word for 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“poor”">&quot;poor&quot;</normalizedToken>
. Because 
<bibRefCitation author="Olivier, E" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" pagination="86 - 93" refId="B43" refString="Olivier, E, 1899. Contribution a l'etude des Lampyrides [Col.], descriptions et observations. Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France 4: 86 - 93" title="Contribution a l'etude des Lampyrides [Col.], descriptions et observations." volume="4" year="1899">Olivier (1899)</bibRefCitation>
originally placed it in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Cladodes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cladodes" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Cladodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Solier, 1849, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" baseAuthorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Cladodes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cladodes pauper" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pauper">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Cladodes pauper</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
would be relatively smaller than the remaining species in this genus, therefore 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“poor”">&quot;poor&quot;</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
<taxonomicName authority="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" authorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Olivier" baseAuthorityYear="1899" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Costalampys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Costalampys pauper" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pauper">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Costalampys pauper</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Olivier, 1899) is unique among 
<taxonomicName authority="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" authorityName="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Costalampys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Costalampys" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Costalampys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. by the pronotum entirely dark brown to black and sternum VI without lantern, in both sexes. 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. pauper" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="pauper">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">C. pauper</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also unique in being restricted to relatively cooler climates, either at sites of relatively higher elevation (&gt;1200m) during the Austral Spring season, or at lower elevations (~600m), during Austral Winter. These observations suggest that this species might be adapted to climates substantially cooler than its congenerics, which deserves further scrutiny.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
